The paper is about ranking in web search, which is a core topic in information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also proposes a new model for ranking, which involves learning the importance of features, and this falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses behavioral economics, which is related to decision-making and optimization (cs.CE). The paper mentions Markov chains, which are a fundamental concept in probability and statistics (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses experiments on commerce search logs, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
